article.headline: Toledo 64, Central Michigan 56
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Keith Triplett scored 16 points and handed out six assists to lead Toledo to a 64-56 win over Central Michigan on Sunday. The Chippewas (7-13, 2-10 Mid-American) held a 45-44 lead with 7:37 left in the game, but the Rockets (10-10, 6-5) went on an 11-0 run to take a 55-45 lead and control of the game. Toledo used a zone defense to stifle the Chippewas' offense and get their second road win of the season. Central Michigan cut the lead to six points with 1:15 left, but the Rockets responded with eight straight free throws on their way to the win. Toledo was 24-of-27 from the foul line in the game. Justin Ingram added 14 points and seven rebounds for the Rockets, while Sammy Villegas scored 11 and Allen Pinson added 10. Giordan Watson led the Chippewas with 21 points and Justin Blevins had 14 off the bench.
